body:
I'm getting a somewhat odd error for the following code. The lifetime bound error happens only for `String` and not for `str`. I'm really unsure whether this is my understanding of lifetimes that is incorrect or a bug in the compiler.

``` rust
fn main() {
    let doc = "<w>werd</w>".to_owned();

    //Remove this line and it does not work:
    let doc = &doc[..];

    let words = doc.match_indices("<w")
        .filter_map(|(i,_)|
            doc[i..].find(">").and_then(|a|
            doc[i..].find("</w>").map(|b|
            &doc[a + '>'.len_utf8() .. b])));

    for i in words {
        println!("{}", i);
    }
}
```

[Playground link](http://is.gd/HlX7Nz)

```
